name: Secrets from the Sky
overview: Secrets From The Sky takes a look at some of the country’s most historic landmarks and glorious landscapes from a bird’s eye view in the sky.

episodes.name: Tintagel Castle
episodes.overview: Bettany and Ben find out more about Tintagel Castle and look at the archaeological evidence that it was once the home of the legendary King Arthur.

episodes.name: Old Sarum
episodes.overview: Bethany and Ben visit Old Sarum in Wiltshire, formerly one of the most important cities in the country. The Saxon kings produced their money there whilst William the Conqueror flaunted his victory over King Harold there as well. The Domesday Book was created in the region as well.

episodes.name: Stonehenge
episodes.overview: The team find out more about the mysteries of Stonehenge, the most famous prehistoric monument in the country

episodes.name: Maiden Castle
episodes.overview: Explore the massive ancient monument known as Maiden Castle, a giant fort carved out of a Dorset hill during the iron age over 2,000 years ago. The aerial investigation uncovers a story of prehistoric life, death and survival as the Romans invaded Britain.

episodes.name: Sutton Hoo
episodes.overview: Our hosts journey to Sutton Hoo in Suffolk, to investigate Britain's very own `Valley of the Kings' - a landscape of mysterious mounds that went undiscovered for 1,300 years and turned out to be the burial grounds of some of the richest Saxon kings.
